\@writefile{toc}{\contentsline {section}{\numberline {2}Method}{1}}
\@writefile{toc}{\contentsline {subsection}{\numberline {2.1}Memory Generation from Training Data}{1}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Overview of the memory-guided LLM re-ranking pipeline. \textbf  {(a) Offline:} Memory is constructed from training data by detecting negation queries, classifying their patterns, and grouping by gold entity type to produce field boost recommendations (Memory v1). \textbf  {(b) Feedback loop:} Self-verification on validation data checks whether reranked top-1 results satisfy negation constraints without gold answers, producing per-group confidence annotations (Memory v2). \textbf  {(c) Online inference:} Test queries are detected, classified, and routed using Memory v2; the matched rule guides document formatting for per-document LLM re-ranking, with hybrid scoring ($\alpha =0.7$) combining LLM and mFAR signals.}}{2}}
\newlabel{fig:pipeline}{{1}{2}}
